The paper deals with stable matching, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). It also introduces a new concept of socially stable matching, which involves modeling communication channels between agents, and this falls under the category of social networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of finding a maximum socially stable matching, which is a problem in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a 3-approximation algorithm, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
